Investigators have identified a gene whose expression confers a growth adva=
ntage to metastatic cancer cells, which cause 90% of cancer-related deaths.
Just another bad day to be cancer! A team of researchers out of Mass Genera=
l have identified the gene that causes metastasis, the spread of cancer cel=
ls from the primary tumor to other parts of the body. Solving metastasis is=
 crucial for curing cancer because it is the primary cause of cancer-relate=
d deaths, accounting for nearly 90% of cancer-related deaths. Our friends a=
t Ezra [ https://substack.com/redirect/834a87c6-5bc3-402e-ab17-02a022104ff5=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] say t=
here=E2=80=99s already a cure for cancer: early detection. But if you=E2=80=
=99re unable to detect cancer early, the ability to stop the spread is your=
 next best solution.
The gene in question is Gstt1, which gives metastatic cancer cells a growth=
 advantage by modifying their surrounding environment. Silencing Gstt1 gene=
 could prevent cancer cells from growing and spreading. Early lab models co=
nfirm this hypothesis. The next step would be developing a therapeutic that=
 can safely and effectively silence the Gstt1 gene.
Fuck cancer. Fuck metastasis. Go science.=20
(2) Gene therapy for hereditary deafness [ https://substack.com/redirect/9e=
2f9b7a-43a2-44b5-b9d1-6de06661b4e8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Carson Smith, Mohammad Faraz Zafeer, Mustafa Tekin in Nature Medicine
Bilateral administration of human OTOF gene therapy appears safe, and preli=
minary data suggest that it could effectively treat a rare form of heredita=
ry hearing loss by enhancing speech perception, sound source localization a=
nd overall auditory experience.
No sir, you=E2=80=99re not at Levi=E2=80=99s but we are still talking about=
 genes.
A study published in Nature Medicine, evaluated the safety and effectivenes=
s of binaural AAV1-hOTOF gene therapy in five children with DFNB9, a form o=
f hereditary deafness. The study found that bilateral injections of AAV1-hO=
TOF into the cochleae restored hearing in all patients without causing seri=
ous adverse events.
Say what?
We=E2=80=99ll say it louder for the people in the back (or who haven=E2=80=
=99t yet received the gene therapy): a new gene therapy restores hearing fo=
r deaf children. Can=E2=80=99t really think of a happier sentence than that=
=2E=20
(3) Advisory Panel of Experts Endorses F.D.A. Approval of New Alzheimer=E2=
=80=99s Drug [ https://substack.com/redirect/c5b22dce-ec39-47fd-91fa-9621a6=
b4abc8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Gina Kolata [ https://substack.com/redirect/0c936b32-9fe3-47d8-934e-f5b8b22=
3f66d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =
and Pam Belluck [ https://substack.com/redirect/479c1378-95f1-4deb-b28f-6b6=
fbcff7cb5?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] for The New York Times
The drug, made by Eli Lilly, is donanemab. It modestly slowed cognitive dec=
line in patients in the early stages of the disease but also had significan=
t safety risks, including swelling and bleeding in the brain. The committee=
 concluded, though, that the consequences of Alzheimer=E2=80=99s are so dir=
e that even a modest benefit can be worthwhile.
If cancer and deafness weren=E2=80=99t enough, it looks like we also made s=
ome progress on Alzheimer=E2=80=99s this week.=20
A committee of independent advisers to the FDA voted unanimously that the b=
enefits of donanemab, an experimental Alzheimer's drug by Eli Lilly, outwei=
gh its risks. The drug modestly slows cognitive decline in early-stage Alzh=
eimer's patients but carries significant safety risks, including brain swel=
ling and bleeding. Donanemab does not cure Alzheimer=E2=80=99s but it does =
slow cognitive decline by about 4=C2=BD to 7=C2=BD months for early-stage p=
atients.
The question was whether that 4=C2=BD to 7=C2=BD slow-down was worth the re=
latively substantial risks of the drug. Alzheimer=E2=80=99s is a nasty, sad=
 disease that currently has no cure. The committee approved the drug becaus=
e, well, it ultimately decided that in the context of Alzheimer=E2=80=99s e=
ven a slight slow down of decline outweighed potential risks.
Donanemab still requires final FDA approval, but when and if it that occurs=
, the drug should become available to early stage Alzheimer=E2=80=99s patie=
nts. Of the current 6 million Americans currently suffering from the diseas=
e, approximately 50% are in early enough stages that donanemab could have a=
 positive impact.
We love to see a common sense risk-benefit analysis [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/2aa6b37f-44c8-49f8-a66d-d7d8a687de7e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] from the FDA that takes both the ri=
sks and the benefits into account. Let=E2=80=99s get this drug live!
(4) LPO Announces Conditional Commitment to Solugen=E2=80=99s Bioforge Mars=
hall for Sustainable Biomanufacturing [ https://substack.com/redirect/ca040=
302-f456-4f87-b5a9-aeda021205c4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]  [ https://substack.com/redirect/ca040302-f456-4f=
87-b5a9-aeda021205c4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
From The Department of Energy
Today, the U.S. Department of Energy=E2=80=99s (DOE=E2=80=99s)=C2=A0Loan Pr=
ograms Office=C2=A0 [ https://substack.com/redirect/ba415253-f84f-4f2d-968c=
-ee423f0f07ba?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Ex=
kRNpU ](LPO) announced a conditional commitment to Solugen Inc.=E2=80=99s w=
holly owned subsidiary Bioforge Marshall LLC (Bioforge=C2=A0Marshall) for a=
 $213.6 million loan guarantee to finance the construction of a production =
facility in Marshall, Minnesota, for bio-based organic acids.=C2=A0This com=
mitment is the single largest U.S. government investment in bioindustrial m=
anufacturing since President Biden signed=C2=A0Executive Order 14081 [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/5305719f-843f-4e28-a026-f9aca9b0bcd1?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] on Advancing Biote=
chnology and Biomanufacturing Innovation for a Sustainable, Safe, and Secur=
e American Bioeconomy.=C2=A0
Build Back Bioforge!
The Department of Energy announced a conditional commitment for a $213.6 mi=
llion loan guarantee to Solugen=E2=80=99s Bioforge Marshall project in Minn=
esota. This facility will produce bio-based organic acids for various indus=
tries, significantly reducing emissions compared to traditional methods. Bi=
o-based organic acids are environmentally friendly chemicals produced from =
renewable biological sources, such as plants, rather than from petroleum-ba=
sed feedstocks.
This project is about as Bidenomics as it gets: American manufacturing, sus=
tainability, supply chain resiliency, DOE Loans, climate!
It=E2=80=99s also a great sign for Solugen, one of the case studies Packy u=
sed in The Techno-Industrial Revolution [ https://substack.com/redirect/45a=
7d235-c806-4c1f-a6eb-338f15a0a635?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZ=
jmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. While the company is presumably receiving the =
loan guarantee because of its potential climate benefits, the real opportun=
ity is in the long term economics: By =E2=80=9Ccutting steps out of the pro=
cess and replacing expensive inputs with technology, which Solugen original=
ly did for the climate benefits, it makes the chemicals cheaper to manufact=
ure!=E2=80=9D=20
Loans can help Solugen scale up manufacturing and bring its chemicals down =
the learning curve towards the =E2=80=9Csoftware-like margins=E2=80=9D of a=
round 60% that its founder Gaurav Chakrabarti told Bloomberg [ https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/9ec9f60a-ef48-4372-826a-c1df1e1ceaac?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] it can achieve.=20
The government won=E2=80=99t back Solugen=E2=80=99s facilities forever =E2=
=80=94 the real win will come when we can manufacture chemicals that are be=
tter for the environment, at home, more cheaply and at higher margins than =
incumbents. Those are the economics that will allow this to scale. And the =
DOE=E2=80=99s loan guarantee is a great step in that direction.=20
(5) We just broke ground on America=E2=80=99s first next-gen nuclear facili=
ty [ https://substack.com/redirect/29caeed2-85cd-405c-b45a-44abf1e78128?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
From Bill Gates
I=E2=80=99m thrilled to see so much economic growth happening, because Kemm=
erer will soon be home to the most advanced nuclear facility in the world. =
I just left the groundbreaking ceremony for the first-ever Natrium plant [ =
https://substack.com/redirect/c7f629b5-2e30-44f4-aaf8-b5af0aa4e28e?j=3DeyJ1=
IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], which will br=
ing safe, next-generation nuclear technology to life right here in Wyoming.=
 It=E2=80=99s a huge milestone for the local economy, America=E2=80=99s ene=
rgy independence, and the fight against climate change.
Speaking of Department of Energy loans, Bill Gates announced the groundbrea=
king of the Natrium plant, a next-generation nuclear facility in Wyoming. T=
he TerraPower-designed plant promises safer, more efficient, and reliable e=
nergy production using liquid sodium cooling. The project was supported by =
the DOE and private investors, like Bill Gates, and is a strong example of =
the type of public-private collaboration that seems to be necessary to push=
 forward these types of large-scale, society-scale projects.=20
That said, TerraPower is just breaking ground on all of the non-nuclear con=
struction. As Gates writes, =E2=80=9CThis step starts the review process at=
 the NRC for the permit application=E2=80=94once it is approved, constructi=
on can begin on the actual nuclear reactor.=E2=80=9D=20
You=E2=80=99d have to think that starting an expensive construction process=
 before receipt of the NRC permit is a sign that TerraPower is confident th=
e permit will be granted, but it may just be the kind of thing you=E2=80=99=
re able to do when you=E2=80=99re backed by one of the richest people on th=
e planet. Here=E2=80=99s hoping it=E2=80=99s the former.=20
If everything goes according to plan, Natrium is expected to be operational=
 by 2030, and should serve as a model for future nuclear projects in the U.=
S.
Bonus: How to do the jhanas [ https://substack.com/redirect/4d6397f1-1c25-4=
