1-be6ab6b9c904?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ]
Packy here. Leaving you with a little nugget for the weekend.=20
I=E2=80=99ve been curious about the jhanas for a couple of years, especiall=
y after Nadia wrote her first essay on them [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/4c353936-8e0d-44c3-8f0a-5263e44f7c16?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], about her experience at a retreat, a coupl=
e months ago. The jhanas, she writes, =E2=80=9Cwhich derive from Buddhism, =
are eight states of consciousness that allegedly produce strong feelings in=
 the body and mind. They can be accessed through a meditation technique tha=
t involves concentrating the mind on an object, then gradually deepening th=
e sensation that arises.=E2=80=9D=20
The internet offers surprisingly little information on how to do the jhanas=
 =E2=80=94 I=E2=80=99ve looked =E2=80=94 so I was very happy to see Nadia d=
rop an essay titled literally =E2=80=9CHow to do the jhanas.=E2=80=9D The p=
iece is clear, honest, and accessible; I can=E2=80=99t yet say if it worked=
=2E I=E2=80=99m going to give it a try tho=
ugh, and passing it along in case y=
ou want to, too.=20
Have a great weekend y=E2=80=99all.=20
We=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox on Tuesday.
Thanks for reading,
Packy + Dan
