he committee approved the drug because, well, it ultimately decided that in=
 the context of Alzheimer&#8217;s even a slight slow down of decline outwei=
ghed potential risks.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Donanemab still requires final F=
DA approval, but when and if it that occurs, the drug should become availab=
le to early stage Alzheimer&#8217;s patients. Of the current 6 million Amer=
icans currently suffering from the disease, approximately 50% are in early =
enough stages that donanemab could have a positive impact.</p><p style=3D"c=
